Meaning: To indicate that a message has been received message and understood.
To indicate that a message has been correctly received.
When used by receiver, to request the sender to repeat the message (“Say again last message”) or when used by the sender to repeat / emphasise the message (“I Say again”)
To indicate that a message has been received, understood, and will be acted upon (short form of “will comply”)
To indicate a pause in a message
To indicate that the signal received is weak during radio check
A To indicate that a collective call is being made to all radio stations in the same talk group
To indicate an emergency message
To preface figures to be announced individually
24 hours time format
To indicate that a message is to be sent
To indicate that the signal received is okay during radio check
To indicate at the end of a message, that a reply is not required, and signifies the end of a call
To indicate at the end of the message and that a reply is required
To signify the intention to check the quality of radio message transmitted and received
Caller uses this to indicate that a message must be repeated by the receiver to ensure it has been received
To indicate readiness to receive a message
To preface the words to be spelt in Phonetic Alphabet
To indicate that a message has been incorrectly received
To indicate ‘.' within a string of digits
